class=" highlight" id="comment-6967"><div
class="commentmeta clearfix"><div
class="gravatar"> <img
src="http://www.gravatar.com/avatar.php?gravatar_id=364d475a3b8af1c8a27fab7c92d30052&amp;size=32" alt="" /></div><div
class="commentinfo"> <span
class="comment_author">Rebecca</span> <span
class="comment_date">May 12th, 2009 at 2:52 pm</span></div></div><div
class="the_comment"><p>That&#039;s not a silly question at all.</p><p>If you want to reuse the oil for frying, you can strain it into a container and keep it in the fridge.</p><p>If you&#039;re ready to throw away your leftover oil, the important thing to remember is NOT to pour it down the sink. Put it in a container, like a leftover milk jug or peanut butter jar, and either toss it out or take it to a recycling center.</p></div></li><li
